a large amount of the US

00:47:47.300 --> 00:47:52.350
population in the nonprofit
government sector.

00:47:52.350 --> 00:47:56.440
And the second thing is that
our tax incentive policies

00:47:56.440 --> 00:47:58.640
would encourage companies,
but not force them,

00:47:58.640 --> 00:48:00.500
to implement these plans.

00:48:00.500 --> 00:48:04.390
So it's likely the people at
the lower end of the spectrum

00:48:04.390 --> 00:48:09.430
might still get lower payments
in profit shares and employee

00:48:09.430 --> 00:48:10.360
ownership.

00:48:10.360 --> 00:48:13.450
The thing I want to emphasize is
that the US government spends,

00:48:13.450 --> 00:48:18.010
as I said, trillions of
dollars every five years,

00:48:18.010 --> 00:48:20.790
over a trillion dollars,
on tax incentives

00:48:20.790 --> 00:48:23.380
and many of these
incentives incent

00:48:23.380 --> 00:48:24.980
concentrated capital ownership.

00:48:24.980 --> 00:48:27.317
We simply want to switch
that-- switch that around

00:48:27.317 --> 00:48:28.650
and then we'll see what happens.

00:48:28.650 --> 00:48:30.720
I will say one thing
that is encouraging,

00:48:30.720 --> 00:48:34.580
in tech for example, managers
with some government support

00:48:34.580 --> 00:48:38.180
early in the '70s and the '80s,
spread throughout the tech

00:48:38.180 --> 00:48:42.270
economy broad-based employee
ownership and profit sharing.

00:48:42.270 --> 00:48:45.190
The Bush administration
came in and did some things

00:48:45.190 --> 00:48:46.870
with the expensing
of stock options

00:48:46.870 --> 00:48:49.340
and not creating a tax
incentive for companies

00:48:49.340 --> 00:48:52.190
like-- that have broad-based
stock options after that, kind

00:48:52.190 --> 00:48:53.130
of destroyed that.

00:48:53.130 --> 00:48:53.870
OK.

00:48:53.870 --> 00:48:56.880
Employee ownership has fallen
about 75% in tech companies,

00:48:56.880 --> 00:48:58.190
just so that you know.

00:48:58.190 --> 00:49:01.860
The Bush administration really
hit tech companies hard.

00:49:01.860 --> 00:49:03.540
So I think we have
to see what happens,

00:49:03.540 --> 00:49:05.873
but we're certainly going to
need things like the Alaska

00:49:05.873 --> 00:49:09.730
Permanent Corporation
to deal with this.

00:49:09.730 --> 00:49:11.609
Yes?

00:49:11.609 --> 00:49:24.690
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]
and you don't really

00:49:24.690 --> 00:49:28.012
talk about that very much.

00:49:28.012 --> 00:49:30.402
How do you propose to get
the political [INAUDIBLE]

00:49:30.402 --> 00:49:33.270
to actually make this happen?

00:49:33.270 --> 00:49:38.010
JOSEPH BLASI: Well,
in three ways.

00:49:38.010 --> 00:49:40.860
First of all, what
is new about our book

00:49:40.860 --> 00:49:45.190
is that we demonstrate to both
conservatives and progressives

00:49:45.190 --> 00:49:48.650
that there is a strong
bipartisan American tradition

00:49:48.650 --> 00:49:50.771
for broad-based
property ownership.

00:49:50.771 --> 00:49:52.270
For those in the
Tea Party, and I've

00:49:52.270 --> 00:49:56.620
spoken to Tea Party audiences,
I will speak to you again

00:49:56.620 --> 00:50:00.950
and say that yes low taxes
and small government is

00:50:00.950 --> 00:50:04.640
right there in the founders
writings when you read it.

00:50:04.640 --> 00:50:08.050
But I also will say the Tea
Party, many of the tea parties

00:50:08.050 --> 00:50:11.727
advocates, forget the third
thing in the founders writings.

00:50:11.727 --> 00:50:14.060
Broad-based property ownership
is necessary for a public

00:50:14.060 --> 00:50:14.560
to exist.

00:50:14.560 --> 00:50:17.982
In fact, the founders believed,
if you read them closely,

00:50:17.982 --> 00:50:19.940
that it was broad-based
property ownership that

00:50:19.940 --> 00:50:23.890
caused low taxes and
small government,

00:50:23.890 --> 00:50:26.480
because households had
enough economic liberty

00:50:26.480 --> 00:50:28.080
they didn't need the
government enough

00:50:28.080 --> 00:50:30.520
and taxes were not needed
for transfer payments.

00:50:30.520 --> 00:50:33.250
So it's a direct
challenge to, I would say,

00:50:33.250 --> 00:50:37.330
a dishonest Tea Party
reading of American history.

00:50:37.330 --> 00:50:39.430
Having said that
though, there is

00:50:39.430 --> 00:50:43.790
an honest Republican
conservative Tea Party

00:50:43.790 --> 00:50:47.240
reading of broad-based
property ownership that I think

00:50:47.240 --> 00:50:49.570
will help them
support these ideas.

00:50:49.570 --> 00:50:52.640
And there is an honest approach
where broad-based property

00:50:52.640 --> 00:50:54.250
ownership fits with
the social justice

00:50:54.250 --> 00:50:58.270
interest of conservatives--
of progressives.

00:50:58.270 --> 00:51:00.490
The second approach
is that, as I said

00:51:00.490 --> 00:51:02.120
and as we show in
chapter three, there

00:51:02.120 --> 00:51:04.890
are a lot of companies in
all parts of the economy that

00:51:04.890 --> 00:51:07.087
do this and we can
demonstrate that this

00:51:07.087 --> 00:51:11.830
is something that could
function acceptably.

00:51:11.830 --> 00:51:15.650
But the third thing really
goes back to your question.

00:51:15.650 --> 00:51:18.150
There really is no
other alternative,

00:51:18.150 --> 00:51:22.840
other than a redistribution or
broadening property ownership.

00:51:22.840 --> 00:51:25.540
And I think that we
have to really get

00:51:25.540 --> 00:51:27.940
those are the two
alternatives or simply moving

00:51:27.940 --> 00:51:29.290
more towards feudalism.

00:51:29.290 --> 00:51:31.970
If people realize, if our
political leaders realize,

00:51:31.970 --> 00:51:33.900
that's the stark
choice than I think

00:51:33.900 --> 00:51:36.590
we might get some
political will.

00:51:36.590 --> 00:51:37.650
I certainly hope.

00:51:37.650 --> 00:51:39.980
If we don't, I think
we're going to have

00:51:39.980 --> 00:51:46.721
a big public fight about this
issue every year going forward.

00:51:46.721 --> 00:51:47.220
Yes?

