Procter and Gamble has
spin offs and acquisitions.

00:52:27.480 --> 00:52:30.960
But specifically focused
on private equity,

00:52:30.960 --> 00:52:34.180
consistent with our
ideas, the special tax

00:52:34.180 --> 00:52:40.570
incentive for
special capital gains

00:52:40.570 --> 00:52:44.360
treatment of the profits
for private equity partners

00:52:44.360 --> 00:52:46.940
in my view should
only be available

00:52:46.940 --> 00:52:50.150
if they have broad-based
share plans in their portfolio

00:52:50.150 --> 00:52:50.860
companies.

00:52:50.860 --> 00:52:53.220
That's an example
of a tax incentive

00:52:53.220 --> 00:52:55.500
which violates each of
those principles of James

00:52:55.500 --> 00:52:57.590
Madison laid it out.

00:52:57.590 --> 00:52:59.330
And it has to be
turned on its head.

00:52:59.330 --> 00:53:01.710
There are ways for
private equity firms

00:53:01.710 --> 00:53:03.980
to use broad-based employee
ownership and profit

