00:54:19.170 --> 00:54:21.980
for 10 seconds to the
cod fishing story.

00:54:21.980 --> 00:54:23.970
Remember, Washington's
legislation

00:54:23.970 --> 00:54:25.440
said that every
ship that went out

00:54:25.440 --> 00:54:29.560
had to have a signed contract
between the captain on the ship

00:54:29.560 --> 00:54:32.070
and all the sailors that
the capital would obey,

00:54:32.070 --> 00:54:34.500
a broad-based profit
sharing contract.

00:54:34.500 --> 00:54:40.010
If you go and look at the
local courts in New England

00:54:40.010 --> 00:54:42.140
you will see that fights
over that contract

00:54:42.140 --> 00:54:45.660
were a common thing between
sailors and shippers

00:54:45.660 --> 00:54:46.160
at the day.

00:54:46.160 --> 00:54:49.200
In other words, some kind of
legal enforcement mechanism

00:54:49.200 --> 00:54:50.030
had to emerge.

00:54:50.030 --> 00:54:53.210
For example, if a
sailor got on in Boston

00:54:53.210 --> 00:54:55.070
and didn't get off at
the end of the voyage,

00:54:55.070 --> 00:54:58.270
but got off Bangor, Maine how
much of the profit share should

00:54:58.270 --> 00:54:59.320
he or she get?

00:54:59.320 --> 00:55:01.940
So I would expect there
would be some legal uptake

00:55:01.940 --> 00:55:05.840
to deal with the changes
that we would have.

