00:55:15.130 --> 00:55:17.890
a raw amount of money.

00:55:17.890 --> 00:55:22.844
there How is it better than
say, just a 20% bump in salary?

00:55:22.844 --> 00:55:25.010
JOSEPH BLASI: Well, the
problem with bumps in salary

00:55:25.010 --> 00:55:28.100
is that we had a
bump-in-salary economy.

00:55:28.100 --> 00:55:31.877
I grew up in the mining region
in Northeastern Pennsylvania--

00:55:31.877 --> 00:55:33.210
by the way thank you for coming.

00:55:33.210 --> 00:55:35.001
I know many of you have
to get back to work

00:55:35.001 --> 00:55:37.425
and I'll conclude
soon-- and we used

00:55:37.425 --> 00:55:39.050
to call it working
for the post office.

00:55:39.050 --> 00:55:40.640
Working for the
post office meant

00:55:40.640 --> 00:55:44.730
that every year your
union got you a 3% to 5%

00:55:44.730 --> 00:55:48.030
real wage increase and you
had a defined benefit pension

00:55:48.030 --> 00:55:52.090
plan that paid you 70% to 80% of
your average of your last five

00:55:52.090 --> 00:55:55.330
income for life.

00:55:55.330 --> 00:55:57.320
Under the protected
economy after World War

00:55:57.320 --> 00:56:01.280
I, where the United States
destroyed all of its enemies

00:56:01.280 --> 00:56:02.830
and was the dominant
power and we

00:56:02.830 --> 00:56:05.660
had trade protections
around our economy,

00:56:05.660 --> 00:56:07.350
you remember those days right?

00:56:07.350 --> 00:56:10.900
The union workers from
AT&amp;T wanted a raise,

00:56:10.900 --> 00:56:12.670
the union would
threaten to strike,

00:56:12.670 --> 00:56:16.090
AT&amp;T would go to the
FCC and get the money,

00:56:16.090 --> 00:56:17.580
and increase your
telephone bill.

00:56:17.580 --> 00:56:18.180
OK.

00:56:18.180 --> 00:56:21.160
That was before globalization
and before deregulation

00:56:21.160 --> 00:56:22.750
and all of these things.

00:56:22.750 --> 00:56:25.500
With globalization and
deregulation and heightened

00:56:25.500 --> 00:56:29.890
competition, there isn't
as much give in the system

00:56:29.890 --> 00:56:32.680
to build all wealth
through wage increases.

00:56:32.680 --> 00:56:34.600
So that's one objection.

00:56:34.600 --> 00:56:37.140
And we have a different
context now, we have as I said,

00:56:37.140 --> 00:56:38.510
we have globalization.

00:56:38.510 --> 00:56:40.730
But there's sort
of a second reason.

00:56:40.730 --> 00:56:43.160
The structure of the
economy has now changed,

00:56:43.160 --> 00:56:45.930
so as I've demonstrated
with these statistics,

00:56:45.930 --> 00:56:50.440
most of the wealth is coming--
so the households that

00:56:50.440 --> 00:56:53.290
are doing best in the economy
are getting that from capital

00:56:53.290 --> 00:56:56.310
gains and grants of
capital ownership.

00:56:56.310 --> 00:56:58.930
If you own the
robots in the future,

00:56:58.930 --> 00:57:00.740
you're going to get some wealth.

00:57:00.740 --> 00:57:03.390
And the amount of
wage increases,

00:57:03.390 --> 00:57:05.960
of wealth increases
coming from labor income

00:57:05.960 --> 00:57:08.600
is going down, whether you look
at the Congressional Budget

00:57:08.600 --> 00:57:10.680
Office or the Bureau
of Labor Statistics,

00:57:10.680 --> 00:57:13.870
the percent of labor income
in the entire economy

00:57:13.870 --> 00:57:15.940
is going down and it
keeps dropping every year

00:57:15.940 --> 00:57:17.440
and this is another
thing that keeps

00:57:17.440 --> 00:57:19.940
dropping as the
internet keeps going.

00:57:19.940 --> 00:57:22.730
Something is wrong.

00:57:22.730 --> 00:57:24.490
So that's my response to that.

00:57:24.490 --> 00:57:27.760
Labor income won't do it alone.

00:57:27.760 --> 00:57:30.800
Although sure, there
clearly are some situations

00:57:30.800 --> 00:57:33.910
where labor income
is unfair, there

00:57:33.910 --> 00:57:35.430
should be a minimum
wage I think.

00:57:35.430 --> 00:57:37.650
I disagree with
conservatives on this,

00:57:37.650 --> 00:57:41.660
and I also think there are some
industries where unions have

00:57:41.660 --> 00:57:46.020
a role to play In terms of
getting fair labor income,

00:57:46.020 --> 00:57:48.930
but in general only
focusing on labor income

00:57:48.930 --> 00:57:53.230
is not going to solve the
middle classes decline.

00:57:53.230 --> 00:57:54.951
Are we at 1 o'clock?

00:57:54.951 --> 00:57:55.450
OK.

00:57:55.450 --> 00:57:57.080
Well I want to
thank you for coming

00:57:57.080 --> 00:57:59.140
and I'll stay around
for a few minutes.

00:57:59.140 --> 00:58:00.920
Thank you so much.

